    "body": "Thanks for the reply.\r\n\r\nHere are some lines from the link you provided above.\r\nIn the worst case, the fallback function can only rely on 2300 gas being available (for example when send or transfer is used), leaving not much room to perform other operations except basic logging. \r\n\r\nSo as it says worst case can get max 2300 means in other words best case will be lesser than that. Also send and transfer are just for example .\r\n\r\nAnyways what can be the methods except send and transfer to send and receive money. I know only two. There are 2 more methods like sendSignedTransaction and sendTransaction, but its not from solidity. They are from web3js. \r\n\r\nAlso 3rd party wallets like metamask and myetherwallet must be using any methods from the above only. (Probably). ",
